TY  - JOUR
AU  - Saez, Emmanuel
T1  - Optimal Income Transfer Programs: Intensive versus Extensive Labor Supply Responses*
PY  - 2002
Y1  - 2002/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355302760193959
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 117
IS  - 3
SP  - 1039
EP  - 1073
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper analyzes optimal income transfers for low incomes. Labor supply responses are modeled along the intensive margin (intensity of work on the job) and along the extensive margin (participation into the labor force). When behavioral responses are concentrated along the intensive margin, the optimal transfer program is a classical Negative Income Tax program with a substantial guaranteed income support and a large phasing-out tax rate. However, when behavioral responses are concentrated along the extensive margin, the optimal transfer program is similar to the Earned Income Tax Credit with negative marginal tax rates at low income levels and a small guaranteed income. Carefully calibrated numerical simulations are provided.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355302760193959
ER  - 



